The paper deals with the problem of sparse approximation, which is a fundamental problem in signal processing and machine learning. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem under different assumptions on the coherence of the dictionary. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of signal processing. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
